A collection of popular knitted nude figures are preparing for the UK's biggest outdoor festival.The woolly group is getting festival-ready for Glastonbury, sporting musical instruments, wellies, flags and even a long-drop toilet.The knits, in a cafe in Shepton Mallet, were created to help raise money for the Dorset and Somerset Air Ambulance.The festival takes place down the road in Pilton, Somerset, and opens its gates on 26 June.Video journalist: Will Richards
